    {
      "id": "mpcd9ydlrgkbkxb8dg9",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 75,
      "y": 1555,
      "strokeColor": "#BF360C",
      "text": "🚨 NO-DEFAULT FITZPATRICK  (D-2026-05-19-012)",
      "fontSize": 15,
      "createdAt": "2026-05-19T08:24:22.089Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-19T08:24:22.089Z",
      "version": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mpcd9ydl9xc4m79vso8",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 75,
      "y": 1580,
      "strokeColor": "#333333",
      "text": "Prototype pre-selected Fitz III; iOS does NOT.\nUser MUST tap a row before the verdict renders.\n\nWHY:  defaulting to III silently inflates the\nestimated safe time for Type I/II users by\n~50%  (MED_III / MED_I = 300/200 = 1.5×).\nThat is a one-way safety error.\n\nEmpty SkinType is a first-class state on\nNowView (\"Pick a skin type to see your\nestimate\"). Anchoring (Tversky & Kahneman\n1974) is real and asymmetric — over-estimating\nsafe time → erythema → melanoma risk.\n\nConvergent signal: Suchi + Linka + Wheeler.",
      "fontSize": 12,
      "createdAt": "2026-05-19T08:24:22.089Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-19T08:24:22.089Z",
      "version": 1
    },
